  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: `Show more` functionality is missing on Status Desktop, that's why long messages are not collapsed and are being shown as is which is not very comfortable. Also we want to align a bit functionality across the platforms. This functionality is present on mobile, so would be nice to have it on desktop as well.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n- long messages are collapsed under `Show more` link (public chat)\r\n- `show more` link is clickable. Upon clicking message is expanded to its full content. Another click collapses the message\r\n- message is autocollapsed when having 50 lines (? @errorists please provide some designs here)\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n`Show more` is not implemented on desktop\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Send long message (50 lines?) to public chat\r\n- Pay attention to message",
